100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On January 19, 1926, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, focusing on disarmament discussions amid rising global tensions. In the United States, the Supreme Court upheld the constitutionality of the Immigration Act of 1924, which restricted immigration from certain countries. Meanwhile, in British India, protests intensified against British colonial rule, with leaders calling for greater autonomy. This period highlights significant international political shifts and growing movements for self-determination.
